  "chapter": {
    "number": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Eliphaz: The Innocent Prosper"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "Then Eliphaz the Temanite replied:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“If one ventures a word with you, will you be wearied?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Yet who can keep from speaking?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Surely you have instructed many,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and have strengthened their feeble hands.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your words have steadied those who stumbled;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you have braced the knees that were buckling.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But now trouble has come upon you, and you are weary.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "It strikes you, and you are dismayed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is your reverence not your confidence,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the uprightness of your ways your hope?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Consider now, I plead:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Who, being innocent, has ever perished?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Or where have the upright been destroyed?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "As I have observed, those who plow iniquity",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and those who sow trouble reap the same.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "By the breath of God they perish,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and by the blast of His anger they are consumed.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The lion may roar, and the fierce lion may growl,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet the teeth of the young lions are broken.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The old lion perishes for lack of prey,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the cubs of the lioness are scattered.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Now a word came to me secretly;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "my ears caught a whisper of it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In disquieting visions in the night,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when deep sleep falls on men,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "fear and trembling came over me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and made all my bones shudder.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then a spirit",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3152
          },
          {
            "text": "glided past my face,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the hair on my body bristled.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It stood still,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but I could not discern its appearance;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a form loomed before my eyes,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I heard a whispering voice:",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "‘Can a mortal be more righteous than God,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or a man more pure than his Maker?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If God puts no trust in His servants,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He charges His angels with error,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "how much more those who dwell in houses of clay,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "whose foundations are in the dust,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who can be crushed like a moth!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They are smashed to pieces from dawn to dusk;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "unnoticed, they perish forever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Are not their tent cords pulled up,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that they die without wisdom?’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
